<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 28 at 3:14PM CDT  by NWS Birmingham</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern Perry
County through 345 PM CDT...
At 313 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Heiberger, or 10 miles northeast of Marion. This storm was nearly
stationary.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Heiberger and Sprott.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
